5|$|Apt Pupil is a 1998 American thriller film {{directed}} by Bryan Singer and starring Ian McKellen and Brad Renfro. It {{is based on}} the 1982 novella of the same name by <b>Stephen</b> <b>King.</b> In the 1980s in southern California, high school student Todd Bowden (Renfro) discovers fugitive Nazi war criminal Kurt Dussander (McKellen) living in his neighborhood under the pseudonym Arthur Denker. Bowden, obsessed with Nazism and acts of the Holocaust, persuades Dussander to share his stories, and their relationship stirs malice in each of them.|$|E
