5|$|During the 43 {{nomination}} years, 151 {{authors have}} had works nominated; 43 {{of them have}} won, including ties. Five authors have won twice: Gene Wolfe, out of eight nominations; Tim Powers, out of five; Patricia McKillip, out of four; Jeffrey Ford, out of three; and James K. Morrow for both of his nominations. Wolfe has the most nominations for an author who has won at least once, while <b>Stephen</b> <b>King</b> has the most nominations without winning, at nine, followed by Charles L. Grant at six and Jonathan Carroll at five.|$|E
